{"title_page": "2017\u201318 Bengaluru FC season", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox football club season\n | club               = [[Bengaluru FC]]\n | logo               =\n | season             = 2017\u201318\n | manager            = [[Albert Roca]]\n | chairman           = [[Parth Jindal]]\n | stadium            = [[Sree Kanteerava Stadium]]\n | league             = [[Indian Super League]]\n | league result      = Runner-up\n | cup1               = [[AFC Cup]]\n | cup1 result        = {{Plainlist|\n* [[2017 AFC Cup|2017]]: Inter-zone play-off finals{{efn-ua|name=fn2|Bengaluru FC advanced to the inter-zone play-off semi-finals during [[2016\u201317 Bengaluru FC season|2016\u201317 season]].}}\n* [[2018 AFC Cup|2018]]: ''Inter-zone play-off semi-finals''{{efn-ua|Bengaluru FC advanced to the inter-zone play-off semi-finals, played during [[2018\u201319 Bengaluru FC season|2018\u201319 season]]}}\n}}\n| cup2               = [[Super Cup (India)|Super Cup]]\n| cup2 result        = '''[[2018 Indian Super Cup|Winners]]'''\n| league topscorer   = <br/>[[Miku (footballer)|Miku]] {{small|(15 goals)}}\n| season topscorer   = <br/>[[Sunil Chhetri]] {{small|(24 goals)}}\n| highest attendance = 25,373 vs [[Kerala Blasters FC|Kerala Blasters]]<br/><small>(1 March 2018)</small>\n| lowest attendance  = 1,051 vs [[Abahani Limited Dhaka|Dhaka Abahani]]<br/><small>(14 March 2018)</small>\n| average attendance = 19,053\n <!-- kit --><!--These kits are based on what the team has said is official. Several variations of these have been used on game day. Please do not edit these.-->\n| pattern_la1 = _blueshoulders\n| pattern_b1 = _bengalurufc_home_2017\n| pattern_ra1 = _blueshoulders\n| pattern_sh1 =\n| pattern_so1 = _arsenalh9800\n| leftarm1 = \n| body1 = \n| rightarm1 = \n| shorts1 = 0000FF\n| socks1 = 0000FF\n| pattern_la2 = _redborderandshoulder\n| pattern_b2 = _bengalurufc_away_2017\n| pattern_ra2 = _redborderandshoulder\n| pattern_sh2 = _red stripes\n| pattern_so2 = \n| leftarm2 = FFFFFF\n| body2 = FFFFFF\n| rightarm2 = FFFFFF\n| shorts2 = FFFFFF\n| socks2 = FFFFFF\n| pattern_la3 = _bengalurufc_third_2017\n| pattern_b3 = _bengalurufc_third_2017\n| pattern_ra3 = _bengalurufc_third_2017\n| pattern_sh3 = _bengalurufc_third_2017\n| pattern_so3 = _bengalurufc_third_2017\n| leftarm3 = \n| body3 = \n| rightarm3 = \n| shorts3 = \n| socks3 = \n| updated = \n| prevseason         = [[2016\u201317 Bengaluru FC season|2016\u201317]]\n| nextseason         = [[2018\u201319 Bengaluru FC season|2018\u201319]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2017\u201318 season''' was [[Bengaluru FC]]'s fifth season as club since its establishment in 2013. This was club's first season in [[Indian Super League]].\n\n==Background==\n{{main article|2016\u201317 Bengaluru FC season}}\nIn '''2016\u201317''' season Bengaluru FC got mixed results. Club failed to defend their league title, finished fourth in the [[2016\u201317 I-League|I-League]].<ref>{{cite news|title=BFC End Campaign In Style, Finish At Fourth Spot|url=http://i-league.org/i-league/bfc-end-campaign-in-style-finish-at-fourth-spot/|accessdate=30 April 2017|work=i-league.org|date=29 April 2017}}</ref> The club did well in the [[2016\u201317 Indian Federation Cup|Federation Cup]], won their second cup title in four years by defeating [[Mohun Bagan A.C.|Mohun Bagan]] 2\u20130 in final.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-india/match/bengaluru-vs-mohun-bagan/2452790/report|title=Federation Cup 2017: Bengaluru FC 2\u20130 Mohun Bagan \u2013 CK Vineeth seals championship victory for the Blues in extra time|first=Manasi|last=Pathak|work=Goal.com|date=21 May 2017}}</ref> Bengaluru FC finished the season well by advancing to [[2017 AFC Cup|AFC cup]] knock\u2013out stage by beating [[Maziya S&RC]] in a must win game and keeping hope alive to better their previous seasons record in '''AFC Cup''' where Bengaluru FC finished runners\u2013up.<ref name=\"AC2017\">{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-india/amp/match/bengaluru-vs-maziya/2383036/report|title=AFC Cup 2017: Bengaluru FC 1\u20130 Maziya S&RC: Sunil Chhetri freekick sends Eagles through|first=|work=Goal.com|date=31 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 May 2017, it was announced by the [[Indian Super League]] organizers, [[Football Sports Development]], that they would be inviting bids for new teams to join the league for the upcoming season. \nBengaluru FC had submitted a bid from [[Bengaluru]].<ref name=\"TOI Bengaluru FC\">{{cite news|title=Bengaluru FC submit bid as ITB submission deadline ends|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/top-stories/bengaluru-fc-submit-bid-as-itb-submission-deadline-ends/articleshow/58851199.cms|accessdate=31 May 2017|work=Times of India|date=26 May 2017}}</ref> On 12 June, it was officially announced that [[Bengaluru FC]] (for [[Bangalore|Bengaluru]]) and [[Tata Group]] (for [[Jamshedpur]]) had won the bids for the new teams.<ref>{{cite news|title=ISL expanded to 10 teams, Bengaluru FC one of them|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/indian-super-league/top-stories/isl-expanded-to-10-teams-bengaluru-fc-one-of-them/articleshow/59113316.cms|accessdate=13 June 2017|work=Times of India|date=12 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Transfers===\n\nDue to the [[Indian Super League]] regulation each  club is allowed to retain a maximum of two Indian players over the age of twenty-one (21). On 30 June, Bengaluru FC announced they are retaining the captain [[Sunil Chhetri]] and [[Udanta Singh]].<ref name=\"Chhetri and Udanta\">{{cite news|title=Bengaluru FC retain Chhetri, Udanta|url=http://www.indiansuperleague.com/press-releases/5572-bengaluru-fc-retain-chhetri-udanta|accessdate=30 June 2017|work=Indian Super League|date=30 June 2017}}</ref> Bengaluru FC also retained defenders [[John Johnson (footballer)|John Johnson]] and [[Juanan]].<ref name=\"Paartalu\">{{cite news|title=Former Brisbane Roar Player Joins Blues On One Year Deal; Juanan Returns To Join Johnson In Defence|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/bengaluru-fc-sign-aussie-midfielder-paartalu/|accessdate=1 July 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com|date=5 July 2017}}</ref> Goalkeeper [[Amrinder Singh]] parted ways with the club. He was retained by [[Mumbai City FC|Mumbai City]].<ref name=\"Amrinder\">{{cite news|title=Indian Super League: Amrinder Singh joins Mumbai City FC in record-breaking deal|url=https://www.goal.com/en-india/amp/news/136/india/2017/06/30/36741652/indian-super-league-amrinder-singh-joins-mumbai-city-fc-in|accessdate=1 July 2017|work=Goal.com|date=1 July 2017}}</ref> Bengaluru FC announced signing of Australian midfielder [[Erik Paartalu]] on 5 July.<ref name=\"Paartalu\"/> Winger [[C.K. Vineeth]] switched the side. He joined [[Kerala Blasters FC|Kerala Blasters]].<ref name=\"Vineeth\">{{cite web|title=C.K. Vineeth Retained|url=https://twitter.com/KeralaBlasters/status/882573885060689920|website=Kerala Blasters (Twitter)}}</ref> On 11 July Bengaluru FC announced signing of Spanish midfielder [[Dimas Delgado]] who last played for [[A-League]] side [[Western Sydney Wanderers FC|Western Sydney Wanderers]].<ref name=\"Dimas\">{{cite news|title=BENGALURU FC SIGN SPANISH MIDFIELDER DIMAS DELGADO|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/bengaluru-fc-sign-spanish-midfielder-dimas-delgado/|accessdate=1 July 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com|date=11 July 2017}}</ref> On 17 July Spanish winger [[Antonio Rodr\u00edguez Dovale|Antonio Dovale]] was signed for a season.<ref name=\"Toni\">{{cite news|title=BENGALURU FC ADD WINGER ANTONIO DOVALE|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/bengaluru-fc-add-winger-antonio-dovale/|accessdate=1 July 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com|date=17 July 2017}}</ref> On 21 July, the club announced retention of under-22 players, defender [[Nishu Kumar]], midfielder [[Malsawmzuala]] and striker [[Daniel Lalhlimpuia]] for a season.<ref>{{cite news|title=BENGALURU FC RETAIN NISHU, ZUALA FOR ISL; DANIEL FOR AFC CUP|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/bengaluru-fc-retain-nishu-zuala-isl-daniel-afc-cup/|accessdate=1 July 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com|date=21 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn ISL draft held on 23 July 2017, Bengaluru FC retained goalkeepers [[Lalthuammawia Ralte]] and Calvin Abhishek, midfielders [[Lenny Rodrigues]], [[Alwyn George]] and [[Harmanjot Khabra]].\nBengaluru FC added eight new players from draft, goalkeeper [[Abhra Mondal]], defenders [[Joyner Lourenco]], [[Rahul Bheke]], [[Subhasish Bose]], [[Zohmingliana Ralte]] and [[Collin Abranches]], midfielder [[Boithang Haokip]] and striker [[Thongkhosiem Haokip]].<ref name=\"Draft picks\">{{cite news|title=BLUES RETAIN FIVE, SIGN EIGHT NEW PLAYERS AT ISL DRAFT|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/blues-retain-five-sign-eight-new-players-isl-draft/|accessdate=1 July 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com|date=23 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nEight players from Bengaluru FC were  signed by other clubs in the draft. Goalkeeper [[Arindam Bhattacharya (footballer)|Arindam Bhattacharya]] signed by [[Mumbai City FC|Mumbai City]]. Defender [[Keegan Pereira (footballer)|Keegan Pereira]], midfielders  [[Eugeneson Lyngdoh]] and [[Shankar Sampingiraj]] were signed by [[Atl\u00e9tico de Kolkata]]. Defenders [[Rino Anto]] and [[Lalchhuan Mawia]] were signed by [[Kerala Blasters FC|Kerala Blasters]] and [[FC Pune City|Pune City]] respectively. Striker [[Seminlen Doungel]] and defender [[Gursimrat Singh]] were signed by [[NorthEast United FC|NorthEast United]].<ref name=\"Draft out\">{{cite news|title=ISL 2017 Draft LIVE: Complete list of players signed|url=https://www.goal.com/en-india/amp/news/136/india/2017/07/23/37264062/isl-2017-draft-live-complete-list-of-players-signed|accessdate=1 July 2017|work=Goal.com|date=23 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nBengaluru FC announced signing of midfielders [[Bidyananda Singh]] and [[Robinson Singh]] for two years on 31 July.<ref name=\"Bidyananda and Robinson\">{{cite news|title=BIDYANANDA, ROBINSON SIGN WITH BENGALURU FC|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/bidyananda-robinson-sign-bengaluru-fc/|accessdate=1 July 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com|date=31 July 2017}}</ref> On  August 7 the club announced signing of Spanish forward [[Braulio N\u00f3brega]] for a season.<ref name=\"Braulio\">{{cite news|title=The Blues strengthen squad further; complete sixth foreign signing|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/bengaluru-fc-sign-spanish-striker-braulio-nobrega/|accessdate=7 August 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com|date=7 August 2017}}</ref> Bengaluru fc added their academy graduates defender Prashanth Kalinga and forward Leon Augustine to the squad for [[2017 AFC Cup]] knockout rounds.<ref name=\"Leon and Kalinga\">{{cite news|title=ROCA ANNOUNCES BLUES SQUAD FOR 2017 AFC CUP KNOCKOUT ROUNDS|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/roca-announces-blues-squad-2017-afc-cup-knockout-rounds/|accessdate=16 August 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com|date=16 August 2017}}</ref> On 17 August Bengaluru FC announced signing of [[India national football team]] goalkeeper [[Gurpreet Singh Sandhu]] from Norwegian side [[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k FC]] for an undisclosed transfer amount.<ref name=\"Sandhu\">{{cite news|title=BENGALURU FC SIGN INDIA\u2019S NO.1 GURPREET SINGH SANDHU|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/bengaluru-fc-sign-indias-no-1-gurpreet-singh-sandhu/|accessdate=17 August 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com|date=17 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 August Bengaluru FC announced signing of Venezuelan international striker [[Miku (footballer)|Miku]] for two years.<ref name=\"Miku\">{{cite news|title=BENGALURU FC STRENGTHEN ATTACK, SIGN VENEZUELA INTERNATIONAL MIKU|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/bengaluru-fc-strengthen-attack-sign-venezuela-international-miku/|accessdate=29 August 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com|date=29 August 2017}}</ref> The club announced signing of  Spanish winger [[Edu Garc\u00eda]] for one year on 3 September.<ref name=\"Edu\">{{cite news|title=BENGALURU FC SIGN EDUARDO GARCIA; FINALISE SQUAD FOR INDIAN SUPER LEAGUE|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/bengaluru-fc-sign-eduardo-garcia-finalise-squad-indian-super-league/|accessdate=3 September 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com|date=3  September 2017}}</ref>\n\nDuring winter transfer window, Bengaluru FC released injured striker [[Braulio N\u00f3brega]] and signed another Spaniard [[Daniel Lucas Segovia|Daniel Segovia]] on 15 February 2018, in a short term deal till the end of the season.<ref name=\"Segovia\">{{cite news|title=ISL 2017\u201318: Bengaluru FC sign striker Daniel Segovia on deadline day|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/news/isl-2017-18-bengaluru-fc-sign-striker-daniel-segovia/70odw0lcppvd1bltd0mi78ry1|date=15 February 2018|work=Goal.com}}</ref> Bengaluru also agreed to the transfer for [[Edu Garc\u00eda]] to [[China League One]] side [[Zhejiang Greentown F.C.|Zhejiang Greentown]] for an estimated transfer fee for $150,000. In the process, Bengaluru FC became the first club receive a transfer fee from a foreign club.<ref name=\"Edu transfer\">{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/news/official-edu-garcia-joins-chinese-zhejiang-lucheng/1dhf3uhdkyt6710vm8drrbg55u|title=Official: Edu Garcia joins Chinese\u2019s Zhejiang L\u01dcch\u00e9ng|work=Goal.com|date=23 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/news/revealed-the-transfer-fee-paid-by-zhejiang-lucheng-to/bhxus7p2altf1regmj8mv6hd0|title=REVEALED: The transfer fee paid by Zhejiang L\u01dcch\u00e9ng to Bengaluru FC|work=Goal.com|first=Ritabrata|last=Banerjee|date=23 February 2018}}</ref> Bengaluru signed Spanish midfielder [[V\u00edctor P\u00e9rez Alonso]] as a replacement on a short team deal for the rest of the season.<ref name=\"Alonso\">{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/news/isl-2017-18-bengaluru-fc-sign-victor-perez-to-replace-edu/lgke3we71mwl1xlz7qgr0bs31|title=ISL 2017\u201318: Bengaluru FC sign Victor Perez to replace Edu Garcia|work=Goal.com|date=2 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n====In====\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; text-align:left\"\n!No.\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n!scope=\"col\"|Player\n!scope=\"c