anced to the inter-zone play-off semi-finals during [[2016\u201317 Bengaluru FC season|2016\u201317]] season.<ref name=\"AC2017\" /> The draw for the Inter-zone play-off semi-finals was held on 6 June 2017. Bengaluru FC was pitted against east Asian zone champions [[North Korea]]n club [[April 25 Sports Club|April 25]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bengalurufc.com/bengaluru-draw-4-25-sc-afc-cup-inter-zone-semifinal/|title=BENGALURU DRAW 4.25 SC IN AFC CUP INTER-ZONE SEMIFINAL|date=6 June 2017|work=Bengalurufc.com}}</ref> Bengaluru FC kicked off its 2017\u201318 season with the home game. Bengaluru FC took the lead against North Korean champions in 33rd minute with [[Sunil Chhetri]]'s penalty. Bengaluru scored two more goals in the second half and took 3\u20130 lead in the first leg.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/bengaluru-v-april-25/report/4g87w3vlyybrfy9n326votazt|title=AFC CUP 2017: BENGALURU FC 3\u20130 APRIL 25 SC \u2013 BLUES CLINCH CRUCIAL FIRST LEG ADVANTAGE IN SHOWERY SEASON OPENER|first=Rahul|last=Bali|work=Goal.com|date=23 August 2017}}</ref> In the second leg, Bengaluru FC managed to hold April 25 to a goalless draw. The home team was awarded a penalty in 75th minute, however [[Gurpreet Singh Sandhu]] guessed it correctly to keep a clean sheet for Bengaluru FC and the team advanced to Inter-zone play-off finals with 3\u20130 aggregate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/april-25-v-bengaluru/4gb8ayys90y9msat12gllltd5|title=AFC Cup 2017: Bengaluru FC through to Inter-zonal final after holding April 25 SC to a goalless draw|first=Ashish|last=Peter|work=goal.com|date=13 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         = Bengaluru FC v April 25\n|date       = {{Start date|2017|8|23|df=y}}\n|time       = {{UTZ|19:00|5:30}}\n|team1      = Bengaluru FC {{flagicon|IND}}\n|score      = 3\u20130\n|team2      =  {{flagicon|PRK}} [[April 25 Sports Club|April 25]]\n|goals1     =\n* [[Lenny Rodrigues|Rodrigues]] {{yel|22}} {{goal|77}}\n* [[Dimas Delgado|Dimas]] {{yel|28}}\n* [[Sunil Chhetri|Chhetri]] {{goal|33|pen.}}\n* [[Harmanjot Khabra|Khabra]] {{yel|43}}\n* [[Udanta Singh|Udanta]] {{goal|51}}\n|goals2     =\n* [[Ri Kang]] {{yel|32}}\n* [[O Hyok-chol]] {{yel|53}}\n|stadium    = [[Sree Kanteerava Stadium]]\n|location = [[Bengaluru]], [[India]]\n|attendance =4,709\n|referee    =[[Turki Al-Khudhayr]] ([[Saudi Arabian Football Federation|Saudi Arabia]])\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=11682&stageid=447&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary\n|result = W\n|mvp = [[Sunil Chhetri]] (Bengaluru FC)\n}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         =  April 25 v Bengaluru FC\n|date       = {{Start date|2017|9|13|df=y}}\n|time       = {{UTZ|17:00|8:30}}\n|team1      = [[April 25 Sports Club|April 25]] {{flagicon|PRK}}\n|score      = 0\u20130\n|aggregatescore = 0\u20133\n|team2      = {{flagicon|IND}} Bengaluru FC\n|goals1     =\n|goals2     = \n* [[Nishu Kumar|Nishu]] {{yel|32}}\n* [[Toni Dovale|Toni]] {{yel|90+2}}\n|stadium    = [[Rungrado 1st of May Stadium]]\n|location = [[Pyongyang]], [[North Korea]]\n|attendance = 6,500\n|referee    = [[Wang Di (referee)|Wang Di]] ([[Chinese Football Association|China]])\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=11684&stageid=447&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary\n|result = D\n|mvp = [[Gurpreet Singh Sandhu]] (Bengaluru FC)\n}}\n\n;Inter-zone play-off finals\nBengaluru faced [[Tajik League]] champions [[FC Istiklol]] in the inter-zone play-off finals. In the first leg, Tajik champions got the better of the visitors and secured 1\u20130 lead with a goal from [[Dmitry Barkov (footballer)|Dmitry Barkov]] in the first half. Bengaluru FC's vocal appeals for a penalty in the injury time were denied by the referee and Bengaluru had to be content without an away goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/istiqlol-v-bengaluru/report/v4buocgymlo1eh5a0i9s1o89|title=AFC Cup 2017: FC Istiklol 1\u20130 Bengaluru FC \u2013 The blues fail the Tajikistan test|work=Goal.com|date=27 September 2017}}</ref> In the home leg, Bengaluru FC gave away an early goal by conceding \na penalty and an important away goal to Tajik team. Bengaluru came back twice from behind but could not overcome the deficit and the game ended at 2\u20132, ending their campaign in 2017 AFC Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/sports/football/bengaluru-fc-vs-istiklol-live-score-updates-second-leg-afc-cup-online-streaming-4896876/|title=Bengaluru FC vs Istiklol, AFC Cup 2017: Bengaluru FC draw 2\u20132 but lose 2\u20133 on aggregate|date=18 October 2017|work=Express Web Desk}}</ref>\n\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         =  Istiklol v Bengaluru FC\n|date       = {{Start date|2017|9|27|df=y}}\n|time       = {{UTZ|19:00|5}}\n|team1      = [[FC Istiklol|Istiklol]] {{flagicon|TJK}}\n|score      = 1\u20130\n|team2      = {{flagicon|IND}} Bengaluru FC\n|goals1     = [[Dmitry Barkov (footballer)|Barkov]] {{goal|27}}<br/>[[Nuriddin Davronov|Davronov]] {{yel|73}}\n|goals2     =\n|stadium    = Hisor Central Stadium\n|location = [[Hisor]], [[Tajikistan]]\n|attendance = 11,000\n|referee    =[[Valentin Kovalenko]] ([[Uzbekistan Football Federation|Uzbekistan]])\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=11686&stageid=447&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary\n|result = L\n|mvp = \t[[Fatkhullo Fatkhuloev]] (FC Istiklol)\n}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         = Bengaluru FC v Istiklol\n|date       = {{Start date|2017|10|18|df=y}}\n|time       = {{UTZ|19:00|5:30}}\n|team1      = Bengaluru FC {{flagicon|IND}}\n|score      = 2\u20132\n|aggregatescore = 2\u20133\n|team2      = {{flagicon|TJK}} [[FC Istiklol|Istiklol]]\n|goals1     =\n*[[Gurpreet Singh Sandhu|Sandhu]] {{yel|3}}\n*[[Rahul Bheke|Bheke]] {{goal|24}}\n*[[Harmanjot Khabra|Khabra]] {{sent off|2|25|42}}\n*[[Juanan]] {{yel|57}}\n*[[Sunil Chhetri|Chhetri]] {{goal|65|pen.}}\n|goals2     =\n*[[Nuriddin Davronov|Davronov]] {{goal|4|pen.}}\n*[[Dmitry Barkov (footballer)|Barkov]] {{goal|56}}\n|stadium    = [[Sree Kanteerava Stadium]]\n|location = [[Bengaluru]], [[India]]\n|attendance = 7,862\n|referee    = [[Khamis Al-Marri]] ([[Qatar Football Association|Qatar]])\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/afcasfeeds?fixtureid=11719&stageid=447&tMode=H&view=ajax&show=matchsummary\n|result = D\n|mvp = [[Sunil Chhetri]] (Bengaluru FC)\n}}\n\n===2018 AFC Cup===\n{{main article|2018 AFC Cup}}\n\n====Qualifying play-offs====\n{{main article|2018 AFC Cup qualifying play-offs}}\nAs the winner of [[2016\u201317 Indian Federation Cup]], Bengaluru FC qualified for AFC cup for fourth consecutive time. They faced the [[2017 Bhutan National League]] champions [[Transport United F.C.|Transport United]] in the preliminary round. Facing crowded schedule in continental games and domestic league, Bengaluru FC fielded an inexperienced squad in the away leg. [[Bengaluru FC Reserves and Academy|Bengaluru FC Academy]] graduate [[Prashanth Kalinga]] made his debut for the senior team. Bengaluru could not capitalize on the chances created and had to settle for a 0\u20130 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/transport-united-v-bengaluru/8to0y7s6u59nrxryfhsbrrgbu|title=AFC Cup 2018: Transport United 0\u20130 Bengaluru FC \u2013 Blues held in Bhutan|first=Nisanth V|last=Easwar|date=23 January 2018|work=Goal.com}}</ref> However, Bengaluru scored a convincing victory in the home leg, with [[Boithang Haokip]], [[Daniel Lalhlimpuia]], and [[Thongkhosiem Haokip]] scoring a goal each.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/bengaluru-v-transport-united/report/8u12zvs4r6kcrjs9dcj8b3aei|title=AFC Cup 2018: Bengaluru FC 3\u20130 Transport United \u2013 Blues clear first hurdle in continental quest|date=30 January 2018|work=Goal.com|first=Ashish|last=Peter}}</ref>\n\nIn the play-off round, Bengaluru FC faced [[2017 Dhivehi Premier League]] runners-up, [[T.C. Sports Club]]. Bengaluru traveled to Mal\u00e9 for the first leg with [[2018 Maldives political crisis|ongoing political crisis in Maldives]]. The first half remained goalless, but Bengaluru scored two quick goals in the second half to take 0\u20132 lead with goals from [[Thongkhosiem Haokip]] and [[Erik Paartalu]], however defensive lapses allowed TC Sports to score two goals and equalize. However, Thongkhosiem Haokip scored again in 78th minute to snatch 2\u20133 victories for the visitors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/tc-sports-club-v-bengaluru/report/1yfea3loscfdvkxijzuuwvqzu|title=AFC Cup 2018: Bengaluru FC sweep away advantage over TC Sports Club in five-goal thriller|first=Ashish|last=Peter|work=Goal.com|date=14 February 2018}}</ref> In the home leg, Bengaluru FC secured a dominant 5\u20130 victory against the visitors as [[Toni Dovale]] scored Bengaluru's first ever hat-trick in an Asian tournament, while [[Erik Paartalu]] and [[Rahul Bheke]] scored other goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/news/afc-cup-2018-bengaluru-fc-demolish-tc-sports-club-storm-in-group-/7j7mlx4v1uu918d36wvnvf3mb|title=AFC Cup 2018: Five-star Bengaluru FC demolish TC Sports Club, storm in group stages|first=Swapnaneel|last=Parasar|work=Goal.com|date=20 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n;Preliminary round\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         =  Transport United v Bengaluru FC\n|date       = {{Start date|2018|1|23|df=y}}\n|time       = 17:30 [[Indian Standard Time|IST]] \n|team1      = [[Transport United F.C.|Transport United]] {{flagicon|BHU}}\n|score      = 0\u20130 \n|team2      = {{flagicon|IND}} Bengaluru FC\n|goals1     =\n|goals2     = \n|stadium    = [[Changlimithang Stadium]]\n|location = [[Thimphu]], [[Bhutan]]\n|attendance = 3,100\n|referee    = [[Sivakorn Pu-udom]] ([[Football Association of Thailand|Thailand]])\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-cup/latest/news/preliminary-stage-saif-sporting-club-limited-0-1-tc-sports-club\n|result = D\n|mvp = [[Toni Dovale]] (Bengaluru FC)\n}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         = Bengaluru FC v Transport United\n|date       = {{Start date|2018|1|30|df=y}}\n|time       = 20:00 [[Indian Standard Time|IST]] \n|team1      = Bengaluru FC {{flagicon|IND}}\n|score      = 3\u20130\n|aggregatescore =3\u20130\n|team2      =  {{flagicon|BHU}} [[Transport United F.C.|Transport United]]\n|goals1     =\n* [[Thongkhosiem Haokip|T. Haokip]] {{yel|26}} {{goal|62}}\n* [[Boithang Haokip|B. Haokip]] {{goal|27}}\n* [[Daniel Lalhlimpuia|Daniel]] {{goal|54}}\n|goals2     =\n* Sangay Dorji {{yel|75}}\n|stadium    = [[Sree Kanteerava Stadium]]\n|location = [[Bengaluru]], [[India]]\n|attendance = 1,167\n|referee    = [[Mooud Bonyadifard]] ([[Football Federation Islamic Republic of Iran|Iran]])\n|report     = [http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-cup/latest/news/preliminary-stage-fc-ahal-2-2-dordoi-fc Report]\n|result = W\n|mvp = \n}}\n\n;Play-off round\n\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         =  TC Sports v Bengaluru FC\n|date       = {{Start date|2018|2|13|df=y}}\n|time       = 21:30 [[Indian Standard Time|IST]] \n|team1      = [[T.C. Sports Club|TC Sports]] {{flagicon|MDV}}\n|score      = 2\u20133\n|team2      = {{flagicon|IND}} Bengaluru FC\n|goals1     =\n* Rilwan {{yel|43}}\n* [[Anatoliy Vlasichev|Anatoliy]] {{goal|71}}\n* [[Ibrahim Mahudhee|Mahudhee]] {{goal|73}}\n|goals2     = \n* [[Boithang Haokip|B. Haokip]] {{yel|43}}\n* [[Thongkhosiem Haokip|T. Haokip]] {{goal|52||78}}\n* [[Erik Paartalu|Paartalu]] {{goal|69}}\n|stadium    = [[National Football Stadium (Maldives)|Rasmee Dhandu Stadium]]\n|location = [[Mal\u00e9]], [[Maldives]]\n|attendance = 890\n|referee    = [[Ilgiz Tantashev]] ([[Uzbekistan Football Association|Uzbekistan]])\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-cup/latest/news/play-off-1st-leg-tc-sports-club-2-3-bengaluru-fc\n|result = W\n|mvp = \n}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         = Bengaluru FC v TC Sports\n|date       = {{Start date|2018|2|20|df=y}}\n|time       = 20:00 [[Indian Standard Time|IST]] \n|team1      = Bengaluru FC {{flagicon|IND}}\n|score      = 5\u20130\n|aggregatescore = 8\u20132\n|team2      =  {{flagicon|MDV}} [[T.C. Sports Club|TC Sports]]\n|goals1     =\n* [[Antonio Rodr\u00edguez Dovale|Toni]] {{goal|12||35||48}}\n* [[Erik Paartalu|Paartalu]] {{goal|36}}\n* [[Rahul Bheke|Bheke]] {{goal|90}}\n|goals2     =\n* Alaaeldin {{yel|37}} {{sentoff|0|61}} \n* [[Ibrahim Mahudhee|Mahudhee]] {{yel|50}}\n|stadium    = [[Sree Kanteerava Stadium]]\n|location = [[Bengaluru]], [[India]]\n|attendance = \n|referee    = [[Turki Al-Khudhayr]] ([[Saudi Arabian Football Federation|Saudi Arabia]])\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-cup/latest/news/play-off-south-jsw-bengaluru-5-0-tc-sports-club\n|result = W\n|mvp = [[Antonio Rodr\u00edguez Dovale|Toni]] (Bengaluru FC)\n}}\n\n====Group stage====\n{{main article|2018 AFC Cup group stage#Group E}}\n\nBengaluru FC competed in Group E alongside [[2016\u201317 I-League]] champions [[Aizawl F.C.]], [[2017 Dhivehi Premier League]] champions [[New Radiant S.C.]], and [[2017\u201318 Bangladesh Football Premier League|2017\u201318 Bangladesh Premier League]] champions [[Abahani Limited Dhaka|Dhaka Abahani]].\n\nBengaluru kicked off their campaign against [[Abahani Limited Dhaka|Dhaka Abahani]] on 14 March 2018. With upcoming [[2018 Indian Super League Final|Indian Super League final]], Roca rested the key players and fielded the reserve side. [[Daniel Lalhlimpuia]]'s goal in the second half proved sufficient as Bengaluru won the game 1\u20130.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/bengaluru-v-abahani/report/64croy0bfifx0vmpsihpeeb8q|title=AFC Cup 2018: Daniel dampens Abahani spirits as Bengaluru open Group E account with a win|first=Nisanth V|last=Easwar|work=Goal.com|date=14 March 2018}}</ref> Bengaluru's game against [[Aizawl F.C.]] was originally scheduled on the first match day, however it was postponed to 5 April due to scheduling conflicts with [[Indian Super League]] and [[I-League]] games. Aizawl took the early lead when they capitalized on the defensive lapse of Bengaluru. However, Bengaluru equalized when they were awarded a penalty just before the half-time. Bengaluru made the most of their possession in the second half and scored two more goals, in spite of missing a penalty, and registered 3\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/news/afc-cup-2018-bengaluru-continue-their-winning-run-by-beating/1gj2umft97ww17ai5xhd6vlme|title=AFC Cup 2018: Bengaluru continue their winning run by beating Aizawl 3\u20131|first=Soham|last=Mukherjee|date=5 April 2018|work=Goal.com}}</ref> Bengaluru then faced [[New Radiant S.C.]] at home on 10 April 2018. Having rested many key players, Bengaluru failed to find many scoring opportunities and Roca was forced introduce [[Sunil Chhetri]] late in the second half and that turned out to be significant as Chhetri managed to shake off his marker in the dying minutes and created an assist to [[Nishu Kumar]] and Bengaluru won the close game 1\u20130.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/bengaluru-v-new-radiant/report/8p1fv2knl1vzu0vfdr9q3ypuy|title=AFC Cup 2018: Nishu Kumar scores last-gasp winner to place Bengaluru FC in driving seat|first=Nisanth V|last=Easwar|date=10 April 2018|work=Goal.com}}</ref>\n\nBengaluru's qualification chances were dealt a blow when they lost 2\u20130 to [[New Radiant S.C.|New Radiant]] in the reverse leg. Both the teams being equal on the points, New Radiant topped the group based on their head-to-head record, leaving Bengaluru's qualification dependent on New Radiant's results.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/new-radiant-v-bengaluru/report/9tpooybhn5hzm3w24m8ko2c8a|title=AFC Cup 2018: New Radiant punish impuissant Bengaluru|work=Goal.com|first=Nisanth V|last=Easwar|date=25 April 2018}}</ref> Bengaluru stayed in contention for the knockout stage with a convincing 5\u20130 win against [[Aizawl F.C.]] that included a brace from [[Daniel Lucas Segovia|Daniel Segovia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/bengaluru-v-aizawl/report/ento8aae4lvc8l98uucby194a|title=AFC Cup 2018: Bengaluru keep knockout hopes alive with a thumping win over Aizawl|work=Goal.com|date=2 May 2018}}</ref> In the final game of the group stage, Bengaluru FC scored a convincing 4\u20130 victory against [[Abahani Limited Dhaka|Dhaka Abahani]], with a brace from the defender [[Nishu Kumar]] and goals from [[Daniel Lucas Segovia]] and [[Sunil Chhetri]]. As [[New Radiant S.C.]] failed to overcome [[Aizawl F.C.]] on the final match day, Bengaluru advanced to the knock-out stage of the tournament for the fourth consecutive year, played in [[2018\u201319 Bengaluru FC season|2018\u201319 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/abahani-v-bengaluru/report/1fsdvrikxoqmjfl23196mwf3e|title=AFC Cup 2018: Sunil Chhetri leads Bengaluru FC to the inter-zone playoffs|first=Nisanth V|last=Easwar|date=16 May 2018|work=Goal.com}}</ref>\n\n;Group E\n{{2018 AFC Cup group tables|Group E|show_matches=yes|showteam=BFC}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         = Bengaluru FC v Dhaka Abahani\n|date       = {{Start date|2018|3|14|df=y}}\n|time       = {{UTZ|20:00|5:30}}\n|team1      =  Bengaluru FC {{flagicon|IND}}\n|score      = 1\u20130\n|team2      = {{flagicon|BAN}} [[Abahani Limited Dhaka|Dhaka Abahani]]\n|goals1     =\n* [[Asheer Akhtar|Akhtar]] {{yel|58}}\n* [[Daniel Lalhlimpuia|Lalhlimpuia]] {{goal|72}}\n|goals2     =\n* Uddin {{yel|88}}\n* [[Ndukaku Alison|Alison]] {{yel|90+1}}\n|location   = [[Bengaluru]], [[India]] \n|stadium    = [[Sree Kanteerava Stadium]]\n|attendance = 1,051\n|referee    = [[Yaqoub Al-Hammadi]] ([[United Arab Emirates Football Association|United Arab Emirates]])\n|result     = W\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-cup/matches/2018/964126\n}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         = Aizawl v Bengaluru FC\n|date       = {{Start date|2018|4|5|df=y}}\n|time       = {{UTZ|18:30|5:30}}\n|team1      = [[Aizawl F.C.|Aizawl]] {{flagicon|IND}}\n|score      = 1\u20133\n|team2      = {{flagicon|IND}} Bengaluru FC\n|goals1     =\n* [[L\u00e9once Dodoz Zikahi|Dodoz]] {{goal|5}}\n|goals2     =\n* [[Daniel Lucas Segovia|Segovia]] {{goal|45+1|pen.}}\n* [[Rahul Bheke|Bheke]] {{goal|63}}\n* [[Daniel Lalhlimpuia|Lalhlimpuia]] {{goal|77}}\n|location   = [[Guwahati]], [[India]]\n|stadium    = [[Indira Gandhi Athletic Stadium]]\n|attendance = 879\n|referee    = Ahmad Ibrahim ([[Jordan Football Association|Jordan]])\n|result     = W\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-cup/matches/2018/964119\n}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         = Bengaluru FC v New Radiant\n|date       = {{Start date|2018|4|10|df=y}}\n|time       = {{UTZ|20:00|5:30}}\n|team1      = Bengaluru FC {{flagicon|IND}}\n|score      = 1\u20130\n|team2      = {{flagicon|MDV}} [[New Radiant S.C.|New Radiant]]\n|goals1     =\n* [[Joyner Lourenco|Lourenco]] {{yel|10}}\n* [[Subhasish Bose|Bose]] {{yel|89}}\n* [[Nishu Kumar|Nishu]] {{goal|90+1}}\n|goals2     =\n* Gotor {{yel|35}}\n|location   = [[Bengaluru]], [[India]] \n|stadium    = [[Sree Kanteerava Stadium]]\n|attendance = 1,839\n|referee    = Hanna Hattab ([[Syrian Arab Federation for Football|Syria]])\n|result     = W\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-cup/matches/2018/964135\n}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         = New Radiant v Bengaluru FC\n|round      =\n|date       = {{Start date|2018|4|25|df=y}}\n|time       = {{UTZ|21:00|5}}\n|team1      = [[New Radiant S.C.|New Radiant]] {{flagicon|MDV}}\n|score      = 2\u20130\n|team2      = {{flagicon|IND}} Bengaluru FC\n|goals1     =\n* [[Ali Fasir|Fasir]] {{goal|30}}\n* [[Akram Abdul Ghanee|Ghanee]] {{yel|34}}\n* [[Ali Ashfaq|Ashfaq]] {{goal|47}}\n|goals2     =\n* [[Lalthuammawia Ralte|Ralte]] {{yel|59}}\n* [[Boithang Haokip|B. Haokip]] {{yel|77}}\n|location   = [[Mal\u00e9]], [[Maldives]]\n|stadium    = [[National Football Stadium (Maldives)|Rasmee Dhandu Stadium]]\n|attendance = 3,112\n|referee    =Khamis Mohamed Al Kuwari ([[Qatar Football Association|Qatar]])\n|result     =L \n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-cup/matches/2018/964141\n|mvp        = \n}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         = Bengaluru FC v Aizawl\n|date       = {{Start date|2018|5|2|df=y}}\n|time       = {{UTZ|20:00|5:30}}\n|team1      = Bengaluru FC {{flagicon|IND}}\n|score      = 5\u20130\n|team2      = {{flagicon|IND}} [[Aizawl F.C.|Aizawl]]\n|goals1     =\n* [[Sunil Chhetri|Chhetri]] {{goal|16|pen.}}\n* [[Daniel Lucas Segovia|Segovia]] {{goal|17||62}}\n* [[Udanta Singh|Udanta]] {{goal|30}}\n* [[V\u00edctor P\u00e9rez Alonso|P\u00e9rez]] {{yel|82}}\n* [[Daniel Lalhlimpuia|Lalhlimpuia]] {{goal|89}}\n|goals2     =\n* Lalrosanga {{yel|71}}\n|location   = [[Bengaluru]], [[India]] \n|stadium    = [[Sree Kanteerava Stadium]]\n|attendance = 1,570\n|referee    = Zaid Thamer ([[Iraq Football Association|Iraq]])\n|result     = W\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-cup/matches/2018/964149\n}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|id         = Dhaka Abahani v Bengaluru FC\n|date       = {{Start date|2018|5|16|df=y}}\n|time       = {{UTZ|19:15|6}}\n|team1      = [[Abahani Limited Dhaka|Dhaka Abahani]] {{flagicon|BAN}}\n|score      = 0\u20134\n|team2      = {{flagicon|IND}} Bengaluru FC\n|goals1     =\n* [[Waly Faisal|Faisal]] {{yel|64}}\n|goals2     =\n* [[Daniel Lucas Segovia|Segovia]] {{goal|13}}\n* [[Nishu Kumar|Nishu]] {{goal|16||58}}\n* [[Sunil Chhetri|Chhetri]] {{goal|60}}\n|location   = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] \n|stadium    = [[Bangabandhu National Stadium]]\n|attendance = 750\n|referee    = [[Suhaizi Shukri]] ([[Football Association of Malaysia|Malaysia]])\n|result     = W\n|report     = http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-cup/matches/2018/964156\n}}\n\n===Super Cup===\n{{main article|2018 Indian Super Cup}}\n\nAs one of the top six teams in [[Indian Super League]], Bengaluru FC qualified for the main round in [[2018 Indian Super Cup]]. Bengaluru FC met the qualifier [[I-League]] side, [[Gokulam Kerala F.C.]] in Round of 16 match. Determined Gokulam Kerala side took the lead in the first half as [[Henry Kisekka]] beat the offside trap to score the goal. Bengaluru's attack in the second half paid off when [[Miku (footballer)|Miku]] scored the equalizer from [[Udanta Singh]]'s assist in the 70th minute. When the game destined to be heading for the extra time, man of the match Udanta Singh scored the goal in the 5th minute of injury time to secure the spot for Bengaluru in quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/bengaluru-v-gokulam/report/2mnhqx4kthzfzp18m5fl3mjca|title=Super Cup 2018: Bengaluru FC 2\u20131 Gokulam Kerala \u2013 Miku bails out Bengaluru|first=Ritabrata|last=Banerjee|date=1 April 2018}}</ref> In quarter-finals game, Bengaluru faced another I-League side, [[NEROCA F.C.]]. [[Sunil Chhetri]] scored his second hat-trick of the season to manage a convincing 3\u20131 victory and set up the semi-final game against their I-League rival, [[Mohun Bagan A.C.]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/bengaluru-v-neroca/report/9f08zv8h3qdqdyq3ewjmz7fu|title=Super Cup 2018: Sunil Chhetri's hat-trick helps Bengaluru topple NEROCA FC by 3-1|first=Ashish|last=Peter|work=Goal.com|date=13 April 2018}}</ref> Bengaluru suffered a setback when Mohun Bagan took the lead just before the half-time and [[Nishu Kumar]] was sent-off soon after the restart. However, Bengaluru continued the attack and staged a convincing 4\u20132 comeback that included a hat-trick for [[Miku (footballer)|Miku]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/mohun-bagan-v-bengaluru/report/123oytn934c0n5ku9qobopw16|title=Super Cup 2018: Mohun Bagan 2-4 Bengaluru FC - Miku nets hat trick as 10-man Blues storm past Mariners|first=Ritabrata|last=Banerjee|date=17 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n====Final====\nBengaluru FC faced yet another I-League side and rival [[East Bengal F.C.]] in the final. East Bengal drew the first blood when [[Ansumana Kromah]] scored a goal from the corner kick, but East Bengal were reduced to 10-men before the half time when [[Samad Ali Mallick]] was sent-off for the violent conduct. Bengaluru dominated the proceedings in the second half as they scored four goals, a brace from [[Sunil Chhetri]] and a goal each from [[Miku (footballer)|Miku]] and [[Rahul Bheke]], and won the inaugural Super Cup 4\u20131. Super Cup also marked Bengaluru FC's fifth trophy in as many years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-in/match/east-bengal-v-bengaluru/report/49qin56qcjcdc5reii52zlq3u|title=Super Cup 2018 Final: Bengaluru ease past East Bengal to register emphatic victory|first=Ritabrata|last=Banerjee|date=20 April 2018|work=Goal.com}}</ref>\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|id= \"Bengaluru vs Gokulam Kerala\"\n|date= 1 April 2018\n|time= 17:00 [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n|round= Round of 16\n|team1= Bengaluru FC\n|score= 2\u20131\n|report= [http://www.supercup.in/news/bengaluru-break-gokulam-keralas-heart-to-enter-quarter-final Report]\n|team2= [[Gokulam Kerala F.C.|Gokulam Kerala]]\n|goals1= \n* [[Miku (footballer)|Miku]] {{goal|70}}\n* [[Udanta Singh|Udanta]] {{goal|90+5}}\n|goals2=\n* [[Henry Kisekka|Kisekka]] {{goal|32}}\n* [[Musa Mudde|Musa]] {{yel|63}}\n|stadium= [[Kalinga Stadium]]\n|location= [[Bhubaneswar]]\n|attendance= 4,233\n|referee= Tejas Visvasrao Nagvenkar\n|result= W\n|motm = [[Udanta Singh]]  (Bengaluru FC) \n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|id= \"Bengaluru vs NEROCA\"\n|date= 13 April 2018\n|time= 16:00 [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n|round= Quarter-final\n|team1= Bengaluru FC\n|score = 3\u20131\n|report = [http://www.supercup.in/news/chhetris-brilliance-breaks-nerocas-resistance Report]\n|team2 = [[NEROCA F.C.|NEROCA]]\n|goals1 = \n* [[Sunil Chhetri|Chhetri]] {{goal|12||55||90+4}}\n* [[Subhasish Bose|Bose]] {{yel|58}}\n|goals2 =\n* [[Pritam Singh (footballer)